The paper proposes a new type of neural network architecture that uses morphological operations as the basic operation in neurons. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses morphological operations in the context of image processing, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the impact of activation functions on network performance, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new type of network architecture that can approximate any smooth function, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SD).
